body:
this means the implementation only supports batchnorm2d, whereas in this model it's 3d.
please build and use the default cpu provider (remove -use_mkldnn option)

btw, the python whl is created and placed under the build/Linux/RelWithDebInfo/dist 
you should install it.

the whl doesn't get created if there are any errors/test errors during the build process.
you can skip tests by adding --update --build options to your build.sh commandline.
